race.description: Reg Nolan - Life Member Maiden Plate
race.comment: LOSEYATOETOE (13) went within a whisker of winning on debut at headquarters and wasn't quite as effective when dropping back to 1100m last time. The quick back-up and rise to 1400m look ideal, and she should bounce straight back to her best. TORPEDOES (9) gave a bold sight at headquarters when rolling along in front before being claimed late by a smart one. He'll spear across again from the draw and ensure a genuine tempo. If left alone, he's capable of pinching it. NAVY ROK (5) was doing his best work late on debut three weeks ago and should take natural improvement. Likely drifts back from the gate and will need the race to set up for him, but he'll be charging late if they overdo it up front. TORRITA (11) isn't doing much wrong and is edging closer to a breakthrough. Freshened and right in the mix. BELONGTOJILL (10) just missed when resuming at Gawler and strips fitter. A key each-way hope who adds value to exotics.
